			<ns0:name>ncb...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/100032148147647801554/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">When updating chrome_rev from 89645 and 89930, chrome_extension_test started failing, particularly on Mac 10.5.

Debugging reveals that the extension is not injecting a bridge script into the main page like it should.  Manually inspecting the extension and the main page reveal they are functioning OK, minus the bridge script.  If the test is reloaded without closing the browser, it will then work.  This bug appears to be a race between the extension loading and the main page loading at startup.

I am disabling this test to roll the DEPS.  Longer term we should:

a) fix the extension race
and / or
b) rewrite the extension test to not rely on a bridge script.  Rather, the extension can manually poll and inject a script into any tab it sees.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-15T22:11:52.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-06-24T00:35:50.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
